[{"id":"VR834497","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a hollow sphere with radius R. A point at the center of the sphere has a charge of negative Q. The charge positive Q is indicated at the surface of the sphere. A horizontal dashed line is drawn through the center point to a distance outside the sphere. Point X is indicated on the dashed line just outside the sphere a distance 1.01 R to the right of the center point. Point Y is indicated on the dashed line a distance 2 R to the right of Point X.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834497.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A negative point charge is at the center of a hollow, insulating spherical shell of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. The point charge has a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative Q\"><math alttext=\"negative Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span>, and there is a net charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> uniformly distributed on the outer surface of the shell. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> is just outside the shell, at a distance of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.01 R\"><math alttext=\"1.01 R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.01</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from the shellâ€™s center, and Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 R\"><math alttext=\"2 R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> from Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span>, as indicated. Which of the following correctly indicates whether the electric field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> is either toward the left, toward the right, or zero?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:40\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:80\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:80\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span></th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span></th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Toward the left</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Toward the left</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Toward the right</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Toward the right</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Toward the right</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Zero</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Zero</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Zero</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR834497_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":3}]